  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">218941_DEC Afghanistan Crisis Appeal Phase I</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In summary, this project aims to provide the following key activities in Herat Province:
 
 1. Health &amp; Nutrition: 3 Mobile Health Teams (MHTs) will be established in 2 northern districts (Kushke Kohna and Kushke Robatsani) and 15 Family Health Houses will be supported to provide maternal and new-born care services in Ghoriyan, Karukh, Zindajan, Enjil, Guzara districts
 
 2. Winterisation: 3000 winter kits will be distributed to most vulnerable women and children, through targeted health facilities
 
 3. WASH: 1 non-functional/damaged water system (solar powered or gravity fed) will be rehabilitated and 3 new solar powered piped water systems will be constructed
 
 4. Protection: Group psychosocial support (PSS) activities targeting boys and girls, as well as monthly support sessions with female caregivers will be provided in two districts (Ushke Kohna and Kushke Robatsani). In addition, cash for protection will be provided to prevent, reduce or mitigate risks identified. These include situations where the concerned individuals or households are at heighten risk of adopting harmful coping strategies if no external support is provided, or when a person cannot access services due to barriers related to costs.</narrative>
  </description>
